Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), dh-sequence-python3, cmake, dh-python, libeigen3-dev <!nocheck>, libpython3-all-dev, python3-all-dev:any, python3-numpy <!nocheck>, python3-pytest <!nocheck>, python3-scipy <!nocheck>, python3-setuptools, robin-map-dev <!nocheck>
Description: Tiny and efficient C++/Python bindings nanobind is a small binding library that exposes C++ types in Python and vice versa. It is reminiscent of Boost.Python and pybind11 and uses near-identical syntax. In contrast to these existing tools, nanobind is more efficient: bindings compile in a shorter amount of time, produce smaller binaries, and have better runtime performance.
Package-List: nanobind-dev deb python optional arch=all python3-nanobind deb python optional arch=all
Testsuite-Triggers: c++-compiler, cmake, g++, libeigen3-dev, libpython3-dev, python3-dev, python3-numpy, python3-pytest, python3-scipy
